         <abstract>
            <p>In this note solutions for the Diophantine equation $$x^3 + y^3 + z^3 = 3$$ are sought along planes $x + y + z = 3m, m \in \mathbf Z$. This was done for $|m| \leqslant 50000$, and no new solutions were found.</p>
          </abstract>
